news.title: Noida: 1,822 Jal Vayu Vihar residents still don't have voting rights
news.para: The impasse between two sections of residents — one who has voting rights and another who doesn’t — is likely to have a binding effect on the daily operations of the society.

news.title: Gurugram: Violating construction ban to attract heavier penalties
news.para: On rampant unauthorised construction in DLF-3 licenced colony, the deputy commissioner asked the district task force to initiate police action and get FIRs registered against the violators.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance plans expansion, aims to raise up to Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: This time, the lender is looking to issue secured bonds to lower the cost at around 8-9%, significantly lower than its offerings of 9.6-10% in July, people familiar with the matter said.

news.title: Proptech startup Propdial raises Rs 1 crore via debentures
news.para: The fresh capital will be used to grow Propdial’s local business and expansion across India. The company, which helps people manage property remotely, had raised seed funding earlier this year.

news.title: CRISIL Ratings revises Phoenix Mills’ rating outlook to stable
news.para: "The outlook revision reflects a strong recovery in retail sales witnessed across malls in the second quarter ending September and October 2021 post reopening after the second wave of the pandemic and an expected further improvement in retail sales in the second half of 2022," the rating agency said.

news.title: Probe former DHFL brass for causing Rs 40,000 crore loss to lenders: Union Bank to CBI
news.para: In its complaint, the lead bank has affixed the findings of audit firm KPMG, engaged by the consortium, which has prima facie found "deviation of laid down norms and procedures, manipulation of accounts, concealments, undisclosed bank accounts and misrepresentation".

news.title: Gurugram civic body relaxes deadline for DLF to complete infra due to construction-ban
news.para: At a review meeting held by MCG officials, DLF representatives submitted that they would not be able to meet the deadline and sought an extension, following which the civic body gave temporary relief.

news.title: NCLAT quashes CoC constitution of Value Infratech, asks NCLT to remove RP
news.para: ​A two-member bench of the NCLAT has also directed the claims of various financial creditors including home buyers should be appropriately fixed against Value Infratech India for its project Skywalk RNE.

news.title: ICRA upgrades credit rating of DLF
news.para: "These upgrades will allow us to further strengthen our access to capital and improve our debt profile in the near term," said Vivek Anand, group chief financial officer, DLF.

news.title: ABL Workspaces raises Rs 15 crore in Series A round from Ethik Inc
news.para: The fresh capital is raised with the intention to expand its seating capacities and centers from 2,470 to 15,000 by March 2023 across the National Capital Region (NCR).

news.title: Even in tech hub Shenzhen, China's property market succumbs to chills
news.para: The lack of turnover in Shenzhen's property market and the fallout on the city's real estate brokers stems in part from deliberate policy efforts over the past year by local authorities to make apartment prices more affordable, including requiring higher down payments for second homes and capping resale prices.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji's Joyville to invest Rs 300 crore to build 750 apartments
news.para: ​Joyville, which is a Rs 1,240-crore platform established by business conglomerate Shapoorji Pallonji, ADB, IFC and Actis, has so far launched six housing projects -- three in Pune and one each in Mumbai, Kolkata and Gurugram.

news.title: Digital Core REIT to raise $600 million in Singapore's biggest IPO this year
news.para: The Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT), which owns 10 freehold data centres in the United States and Canada worth around $1.4 billion, is issuing 682 million units at $0.88 per a piece, excluding a greenshoe option worth $47 million.

news.title: Asian Paints to invest Rs 960 crore to expand its manufacturing capacity in Gujarat
news.para: The company has proposed to expand its manufacturing capacity of paint from 130,000 KL to 250,000 KL and resins and emulsions from 32,000 MT to 85,000 MT which will be completed over a period of the next 2-3 years.

news.title: Mumbai’s stuck housing redevelopment projects to get a push
news.para: The state government decides to help resolve issues that have stalled over 550 housing projects by playing a facilitator’s role
